That's what makes Election so much more insightful than Primary Colors : Tracy isn't fatted and self-satisfied like Nichols' version of Clinton.
Unlike Mike Nichols' glib Primary Colors (1998), which seized every opportunity to take cheap shots at its characters, Payne seizes every opportunity to give his characters more dimension.
